Ten people sustained injuries on Umgeni Road when a taxi collided with a car near North Coast Road in Durban on Thursday morning.Ten injured in Umgeni Road taxi collision https://t.co/GzGnF1xFlN @ER24EMS #ArriveAlive pic.twitter.com/4ATFE5kQxK&mdash; Arrive Alive (@_ArriveAlive) January 12, 2017Paramedics found the taxi off the road into nearby trees. Ten people were found with minor to moderate injuries.All patients were treated and transported to Addington Hospital.,it is believed that the accident happened at 6.30am in the morning. Paramedics treated the injured for scrapes and bruises before they were transported to Addington Hospital, ER24 said in statement.None of the occupants in the light motor vehicle sustained any injuries.-TNA Reporter